headroom-core (vendored, feature-trimmed)
=========================================

This directory contains a vendored copy of the `headroom-core` crate.

Source repository: https://github.com/hybloid/headroom
Source commit:     6d3f39f213f4eb2d1c6c814b34e1bf6fe2a5c959
Vendored path:     crates/headroom-core (src/ + Cargo.toml + config/)
Original license:   Apache-2.0 (see LICENSE in this directory)
Copyright 2025 Headroom Contributors

Modifications
-------------

This copy has been MODIFIED for use in poverty-mode. The changes are
limited to feature-trimming and de-workspacing; the compression API
(`headroom_core::transforms::compress_anthropic_live_zone` and the
live-zone dispatcher) is unchanged. Specifically:

1. De-workspaced `Cargo.toml`: every `*.workspace = true` key was
   replaced with a concrete value (license = "Apache-2.0",
   edition = "2021", rust-version, a version, and concrete dependency
   specifications), and workspace-only keys were removed, so the crate
   builds standalone as a local path dependency.

2. Made the ONNX / embedding / HuggingFace dependencies
   (`magika`, `fastembed`, `hf-hub`, `tokenizers`) OPTIONAL and gated
   them behind non-default cargo features (`magika`, `embeddings`,
   `hf-tokenizers`). The new `transforms-min` feature (selected by
   poverty-mode) excludes all of them, so the ONNX runtime is not
   pulled into the dependency graph.

3. cfg-gated the modules, re-exports, and call sites that reference
   those crates (`transforms::detection`, `transforms::magika_detector`,
   `relevance::embedding`, `relevance::hybrid`, the HuggingFace tokenizer
   adapter, and the SmartCrusher default-scorer construction), with a
   pure-Rust BM25 fallback for the relevance scorer so the live-zone
   compression path still functions when ONNX is absent.

The live-zone path (the dispatcher, the regex `content_detector`, the
per-content-type compressors, the arithmetic / tiktoken tokenizer
estimators, and the BM25 relevance scorer) compiles and works under the
default `transforms-min` feature with no ONNX dependency.
